[h1]1.2 - Bug Fixes & Culture Restrictions[/h1]

[list]
[*]Fixed [b]crash bug[/b] in AI pop control: the trigger referenced a player-scoped variable ([i]var:noble_auto_marry_pop_limit[/i]) instead of the correct global variable ([i]global_var:noble_auto_marry_pop_limit_for_ai[/i]), causing script errors and crashes for AI countries
[*]Fixed [b]AI population limit not working[/b]: the AI on_actions used [i]has_variable[/i] (country-scoped) to check a global variable, so the pop limit was silently ignored and AI marriages always proceeded regardless of the configured limit
[*]Added [b]character_can_marry_trigger[/b] checks to all marriage effects for patch 1.1 compatibility, respecting [i]blocked_from_marriage[/i] modifiers and marriage slot availability
[*]Added [b]Culture Restriction Settings[/b]: a new configuration option allowing you to restrict automatic marriages by culture. Three modes available:
  [list]
  [*]No restriction (default) - courtiers of any culture may marry
  [*]Primary, Accepted, and Tolerated cultures only
  [*]Primary culture only
  [/list]
[/list]
